headline: Alphabet (Google) Stock Investors Just Got More Bad News From a Federal Judge
summary: In 2020, the Justice Department sued Google, a subsidiary of Alphabet (NASDAQ: GOOGL) (NASDAQ: GOOG), accusing the company of operating an illegal monopoly in online search.  In 2023, the Justice Department filed another lawsuit, accusing the company of operating an illegal monopoly in adtech software.  Federal judges have since ruled against Alphabet in both antitrust cases.
